AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - ASIA (34): CHINA (SHAANXI) DOMESTIC SWINE, (HEILONGJIANG) FARMED WILD BOAR
************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 4 Dec 2018
Source: Yicai Global (Shanghai) [summ., edited]
https://yicaiglobal.com/news/china-discovers-more-african-swine-fever-in-beijing


China's agriculture ministry has found more [outbreaks] of African swine fever [ASF] in Beijing, adding to the more than 70 [outbreaks] already found across the country since August [2018].

In the latest case, some 85 of 9835 [susceptible] hogs were infected and 17 died in the capital's Tongzhou district, Beijing Business Daily reported, citing the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs. Other infected pigs were also found in Xi'an, Shaanxi province [see comment below] and at a wild boar farm up north in Heilongjiang.

It is the 2nd discovery of the epidemic in Beijing over the past few weeks, after 2 farms in Fangshan district were found to be infected on 23 Nov 2018. Other cases have been found in Tianjin, Jiangxi, Hubei, Inner Mongolia and other cities during the same period, as the ministry's website shows.

The speed at which the virus is spreading should slow down, according to Li Guoxiang, a researcher at the Chinese Academy of Sciences, which should prevent the price of pork falling further and stop more farms from closing their doors.

[Byline: Dou Shicong; editor: James Boynton]

